# prototype-consumer

This directory is a scratch space for testing `bunx shadcn add` against
the local registry. It is gitignored except for this README.

## Usage

```bash
# Terminal 1: build + serve via the site dev server
cd ../site
bun run dev   # serves site/public/r/* at http://localhost:3000

# Terminal 2: simulate a real consumer
cd prototype-consumer
bun init -y
echo '{"$schema":"https://ui.shadcn.com/schema.json","style":"default","rsc":false,"tsx":true,"tailwind":{"config":"","css":"","baseColor":"neutral","cssVariables":false},"aliases":{"components":"src/cli","utils":"src/cli/lib","lib":"src/cli/lib","hooks":"src/cli/hooks","ui":"src/cli/ui"}}' > components.json

# Note: registry.json now ships prod URLs, so registryDependencies will
# resolve to https://cligentic.railly.dev. To test a fully local chain,
# rebuild with the placeholder URL substituted, or rely on prod for deps:
bunx shadcn@latest add http://localhost:3000/r/killswitch.json  # no deps, fully local
bunx shadcn@latest add http://localhost:3000/r/next-steps.json  # local + prod deps
```
